	<h2>Cancellations</h2>

	Sidestage has a simple cancellation policy in place to protect artists. If you cancel a confirmed booking, you are entitled to a refund as follows:<br>

	<ul>
		<li>To get a full refund, cancel 2 weeks in advance. For example, if the event is on Friday the 15th, you would need to cancel by Friday the 1st.</li>
		<li>To get a 50% refund, cancel 3 days in advance. For example, if your event is on Friday evening, you would need to cancel by Tuesday evening.</li>
		<li>No refund if you cancel less than 24 hours in advance. For example, if your event is Friday evening, and you cancel Friday morning.</li>
	</ul> 
	<br>
	Bookings that have not been confirmed can be cancelled for free. Sidestage does not bill your credit card until a booking is confirmed.<br>
	 
	If an artist cancels:<br>

	<ul>
		<li>A full refund will be given</li>
	</ul>
	<br>
	Sidestage will mediate when necessary and has final say in all disputes.<br><br><br>

